data.title: OUR DOCTORS ‹ Lotus Medical
data.text:
DR. NAM PHUONG JULIE NGUYEN

Dr. Nguyen was born and raised in Montréal, Québec. She completed her medical school in 2007 and Family Medicine residency in 2009 at the Université de Montréal. After graduating, she relocated to beautiful Vancouver. She is the medical director and owner of Lotus Medical. She is the medical consultant for the French Consulate (Vancouver office) and is member of the IT committee for the Vancouver Division of Family Practice. She speaks English, French and Vietnamese.

Dr. JANE GUSTAFSON

Dr. Gustafson grew up in South Surrey, British Columbia. She obtained her Bachelor of Science Degree at the University of Victoria. She later completed her medical school in 2013 and Family Medicine Residency in 2015 at the University of British Columbia. Dr. Gustafson lives in Vancouver and has been building her Family Practice here since 2015. Outside of her Family Practice work at Lotus Medical, she works as a locum physician at Vancouver Youth Clinics and is a Clinical Instructor for 1st and 2nd year UBC Medical Students.
